accessrestrict.p: Open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Henry Luce Foundation was established by Henry R. Luce in 1936. As a New York-based nonprofit organization, the Luce Foundation awards grants in American Art, Asian studies, Higher Education, Theology, and supports the Clare Boothe Luce Program for women in science, mathematics, and engineering.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series includes grant files and reports for the first grouping of American educational institutions that were invited to participate in newly established Clare Boothe Luce Fund.
